<hr size=6 align=center width=65%>
<center><table width=65%><tr valign=top><td valign=top width=30%>
<p><b>Gun law</b> &nbsp; In spite of a rebellion by four Tory backbenchers, the government defeated an opposition amendment which would have banned civilian ownership of all handguns. The government's bill, tightening restrictions on gun ownership, passed.<br>
<p><b>Parting shot</b> &nbsp; John Donnelly resigned as chairman of Mil-Tec Corporation after the firm was accused of supplying arms to Hutu militias in Rwanda.<br>
<p><b>Tony's donors</b> &nbsp; It was revealed that several business executives, including Sir Trevor Chinn, chairman of Lex Service, and Sir Emmanuel Kaye, a former truck-company boss, had made secret donations to a fund which finances the office of Tony Blair, Labour's leader.<br>
<p><b>Pre-emptive strike</b> &nbsp; The government announced proposals to allow employers and the public to sue unions over "disproportionate and excessive" strikes which affect public services.<br>
</td><td width=5%></td><td valign=top width=30%>
<p><b>Shorter sentences</b> &nbsp; The High Court ruled that the methods used over the past 30 years for calculating the release dates of prisoners serving concurrent sentences were wrong. Around 800 prisoners will be released early as a result, and thousands of former inmates may sue for compensation.<br>
<p><b>Also free</b> &nbsp; Karamjit Singh, Britain's longest-serving remand prisoner, who has spent six years in jail awaiting deportation for alleged terrorist activities, was freed after the European Court of Human Rights ruled that he risked being killed if sent back to India.<br>
<p><b>Plots uncovered</b> &nbsp; The Royal Ulster Constabulary said it had discovered <font size=-1>IRA</font> plans to murder Sir Brian Hutton, Northern Ireland's Lord Chief Justice, and that it had intercepted an attempted land-mine attack on security forces near Londonderry.<br>
<p><b>UFO</b> &nbsp; Michael Knighton threatened to resign as chairman of Carlisle United Football Club after being ridiculed over his claim to have seen a flying saucer which sent him a telepathic message.<br>

</td></tr></table></center>

