<hr size=6 align=center width=65%>
<center><table width=65%><tr valign=top><td valign=top width=30%>
 
<p><b>Progress</b> &nbsp; The first discussions on decommissioning weapons were held at the talks on the future of Northern Ireland between the Ulster Unionists and the nationalist <font size=-1>SDLP</font>. Sinn Fein, the political wing of the <font size=-1>IRA</font>, is excluded.<br>
<p><b>Checkout checkups</b> &nbsp; The government announced further National Health Service reforms, including the possibility of surgeries in supermarkets.<br>
<p><b>Defector</b> &nbsp; Peter Thurnham, a rebel Conservative <font size=-1>MP</font> who resigned the party whip in February, defected to the Liberal Democrats.<br>
<p><b>Merciful release</b> &nbsp; A Scottish man who killed his brother to end his suffering from an incurable illness was set free after admitting culpable homicide.<br>
<p><b>Closed loop</b> &nbsp; The government promised to close a legal loophole in which money transferred between accounts by cheque or electronic means is not recognised as "property", making it hard to prosecute for mortgage fraud.<br>
</td><td width=5%></td><td valign=top width=30%>
<p><b>Life and death</b> &nbsp; A court refused to allow a widow to be artifically inseminated with the sperm of her late husband because he had not given written permission.<br>
<p><b>Reunited</b> &nbsp; Claire Short, a Labour front-bencher, has met up with her son, who she put up for adoption when he was six weeks old. He is a Tory lawyer, who says he is veering towards Labour. <br>
<p><b>Demon Damon</b> &nbsp; Damon Hill followed in the footsteps of his late father Graham Hill by winning motor racing's Formula One world championship.<br>
<p><b>Rat-catchers caught</b> &nbsp; John Clark, who was sacked as chief executive of <font size=-1>BET</font>, a business-services group, when it was taken over by Rentokil, a pest-control company, won &#163;3m compensation.<br>
<p><b>Amazing underpants</b> &nbsp; The Townswomen's Guild issued a booklet on personal safety which suggested that women living alone should hang a pair of men's <font size=-1>Y</font>-fronts on their washing lines to deter would-be attackers.<br>

